The paper discusses a novel distributed online learning algorithm that uses differential privacy to preserve the privacy of learners. This algorithm is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories that this paper belongs to, ordered from most to least likely.
